I"U<p>Once the nation’s best conferences year in and year out — the Big East remains that league in name alone. Gone are many of the team’s that made it famous throughout it’s heyday from the mid-80s and into the early 2010s. Still, this 10-team league, which features the seven Catholic universities from the Big East of yesteryear, and three of the 21st centuries most pesky mid-major programs — Butler, Creighton and Xavier. The Big East is more than capable of producing its fair share of dangerous squads come tournament time. Let’s preview the 2014-15 season for The Big East.</p>
